---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Kitchen Renovations Belconnen | 1970s–80s Homes"
  description="Kitchen renovations in Belconnen — custom cabinetry, stone benchtops and full renovations for the district's original 1970s–80s homes. ACT-licensed builders. Free measure &amp; quote."
  canonical="https://kitchenrenovationscanberra.com.au/belconnen/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Belconnen &middot; Bruce &middot; Florey &middot; Kaleen &middot; Hawker</span>
      <h1>Kitchen renovations in <span class="accent">Belconnen</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Belconnen is one of Canberra&rsquo;s largest districts &mdash; a sweep of
        1970s and 80s suburbs where a huge share of homes still have their
        original kitchen. We renovate them properly: custom cabinetry, compliant
        stone benchtops, and full strip-out renovations that open dated kitchens
        to the living areas.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Belconnen</span>
      <h2>The Belconnen kitchen story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>A district built in the 1970s and 80s &mdash; and it shows in the kitchens.</h3>
        <p>
          Belconnen took shape as a major Canberra district through the 1970s
          and into the 80s, and that era defines its housing: freestanding brick
          homes and townhouse complexes across Kaleen, Florey, Bruce, Hawker,
          Holt and Page. A large proportion still have their <strong>original
          kitchen</strong> &mdash; laminate benchtops, dated cabinetry, closed-off
          galley layouts that don&rsquo;t suit how families live now. These are
          the kitchens we&rsquo;re renovating most across Belconnen.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Opening up the closed 80s layout.</h3>
        <p>
          The single most-requested Belconnen renovation is opening a closed
          kitchen to the living and dining area. That often involves removing or
          modifying a wall, which can be load-bearing &mdash; so it brings
          structural work and likely <strong>ACTPLA building approval</strong>
          into the job. We <a href="/services/kitchen-design/">design</a> the
          options in 3D, advise exactly where approval and a building certifier
          are needed, and never quietly skip that step to win the work.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Townhouse &amp; freestanding mix.</h3>
        <p>
          Belconnen has a strong mix of freestanding homes and 1970s&ndash;80s
          townhouse complexes. Townhouses can have body-corporate rules around
          structural changes and noise, and shared services to work around;
          freestanding homes give more freedom to reconfigure. We tailor the
          plan to which you have &mdash; and to the non-standard cabinet openings
          common in this era, where <a href="/services/custom-cabinetry/">custom
          cabinetry</a> fits far better than flat-pack.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Asbestos caution in older Belconnen homes.</h3>
        <p>
          Some Belconnen homes pre-date the mid-1980s and can contain bonded
          asbestos in wall sheeting, vinyl floor backing and old splashbacks, and
          the broader ACT carries the Mr Fluffy loose-fill asbestos legacy
          (insulation installed 1968&ndash;1980). Before any demolition we
          identify suspect materials and arrange licensed testing and removal
          where needed. It&rsquo;s built into the program honestly, not sprung on
          you mid-job.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Belconnen kitchen jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Full renovation of an original 1980s kitchen, opened to the living area ($30K&ndash;$55K)</li>
          <li>Custom cabinetry and a porcelain benchtop in a Kaleen family home</li>
          <li>Budget makeover &mdash; new doors, benchtop and splashback &mdash; on a sound 80s kitchen (from ~$8,800)</li>
          <li>Townhouse kitchen reconfiguration within body-corporate rules</li>
          <li>Walk-in or butler&rsquo;s pantry added during a full renovation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/gungahlin/">Gungahlin</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/tuggeranong/">Tuggeranong</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/woden/">Woden</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/dickson/">Dickson</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/canberra-region/">All Canberra &amp; the ACT</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Belconnen kitchen quote.</h2>
        <p>1970s&ndash;80s renovation specialists. Open-plan conversions, custom cabinetry, fixed-price quotes.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
